                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 741.8215/48.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British Government objects to G. Mason, alleging incompetency. [Appointment on
                    the boundary commission.] Appointment another surveyor imperative. Boundary
                    Commission ready to proceed. Expense delay chargeable to the Liberian
                    Government. Liberian President requests me to ascertain whether Captain Young
                    may serve as Liberian Commissioner. Believe British Government would appreciate
                    such service.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
